# shadcn/ui Component Guidelines

## IMPORTANT: Always Prioritize shadcn/ui Components

When implementing ANY UI elements, you MUST:

1. **Use shadcn/ui components first** - Always check if a shadcn/ui component exists before writing custom HTML
2. **Install new components when needed** - If a component doesn't exist in the project, install it using the command below
3. **Limit raw HTML usage** - Only use raw HTML when absolutely necessary (e.g., semantic structure, layouts). For interactive elements, forms, cards, buttons, badges, etc., ALWAYS use shadcn/ui components
4. **Compose components** - Combine multiple shadcn/ui components to create rich UIs instead of writing custom HTML/CSS

## Installing shadcn/ui Components

Use the latest version of shadcn to install new components:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]
```

Examples:
```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
npx shadcn@latest add card
npx shadcn@latest add badge
npx shadcn@latest add dialog
npx shadcn@latest add form
npx shadcn@latest add input
npx shadcn@latest add select
npx shadcn@latest add table
```

## Available shadcn/ui Components

Before implementing UI, check if these components are available:
- **Layout**: Card, Separator, Aspect Ratio, Scroll Area
- **Forms**: Button, Input, Textarea, Checkbox, Radio Group, Select, Switch, Slider, Label, Form
- **Data Display**: Table, Badge, Avatar, Skeleton, Progress
- **Feedback**: Alert, Alert Dialog, Toast, Dialog, Sheet
- **Navigation**: Tabs, Dropdown Menu, Command, Navigation Menu
- **Overlays**: Dialog, Sheet, Popover, Tooltip, Hover Card

Full list: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components

## Example: Good vs Bad Practice

❌ **BAD** - Using raw HTML:
```tsx
<div className="border rounded-lg p-4">
  <button className="bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">
    Click me
  </button>
</div>
```

✅ **GOOD** - Using shadcn/ui:
```tsx
import { Card } from '@/components/ui/card'
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'

<Card className="p-4">
  <Button>Click me</Button>
</Card>
```

## When to Use Raw HTML

Only use raw HTML for:
- Semantic structure (main, section, article, header, footer)
- Simple layout containers (div, span) when no component alternative exists
- Text content (p, h1-h6) without styling needs
- Lists (ul, ol, li) for simple content

## Always Ask First

If you're unsure whether a shadcn/ui component exists for your use case:
1. Check the documentation: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components
2. Install the component if it exists
3. Only use custom HTML as a last resort
